The @fixtureLoader.load()@ method can also be used to define a one time fixute inlineâ€¦

{code}
def fixture = fixtureLoader.load {
	guillaume(Author) {
		name = "Guillaume Laforge"
	}
	dierk(Author) {
		name = "Dierk Koenig"
	}
	gina(Book) {
		title = "Groovy In Action"
		authors = [guillaume, dierk]
	}
}
{code}

You can post-process inline fixutres with Groovy's @with@ mechanism...

{code}
fixtureLoader.load {
	log(LogMessage) {
		message = "something happened"
	}
}.with {
	// change the creation date of the log message
	log.dateCreated -= 1
	log.save()
}
{code}
